    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-20T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-20T04:00:00-05:00" n="177"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d177">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5427: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tientsin (<persName type="from">Ward</persName>)
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-20T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 20, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 20—8:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The following telegram has been sent to the Legation: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“July 20, 4 p.m. Reliably informed that 10 troop trains of <persName
                                corresp="frus1932v03#p_CC2">Chang</persName>’s forces have already
                            passed through Tientsin for Tungchow and vicinity with 10 to 15 more
                            expected.</p>
                        <p>Informant credibly states that Japanese commanding officer at Chinchow,
                            Liaoning, sent one infantry regiment each to Chaoyang and the northeast
                            of Peipiao, at which last point according to unconfirmed reports they
                            are engaged with Jehol Regular Cavalry Regiment from Peipiao and 214th
                            Regiment Jehol Regulars from Chaoyang.</p>
                        <pb facs="0271" n="173" xml:id="pg_173"/>
                        <p>Japanese sources state that entry into Jehol from Chaoyang will require
                            at least two divisions.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to the Department and Nanking.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ward</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
